<h2 style=3D"font-weight: bold; font-family: &quot;Arial Black&quot;, Arial=
, Helvetica, sans-serif; letter-spacing: -1px; font-size: 20px; border-bott=
om-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: dotted; margin: 0px; padding: 16px 0px =
5px;">Two Sigma</h2>
</td>
</tr>
</table>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">There are two paradigmatic ways to run a hedge=
 fund:</p>
<ol style=3D"list-style-type: decimal; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;"=
>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Pirate captain with a pirate crew; or=
</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Institutional firm with professio=
nal management, well-defined career paths and succession plans, replicable =
processes that do not depend on the genius of the charismatic founder, etc.=
</li>
</ol>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Most hedge funds start as pirate crews, and th=
en if they get big and successful enough the interesting question is whethe=
r they can successfully make the transition to being permanent institutiona=
l firms. A weirder model, though,=C2=A0is=C2=A0<em>two=C2=A0</em>charismati=
c pirate captains with=C2=A0<em>two=C2=A0</em>pirate crews who are=C2=A0<a =
href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/31848390.258405/aHR0c=
HM6Ly93d3cud3NqLmNvbS9hcnRpY2xlcy9pbnNpZGUtdGhlLWVzY2FsYXRpbmctZmV1ZC1hdC1v=
bmUtb2Ytd2FsbC1zdHJlZXRzLWJpZ2dlc3QtaGVkZ2UtZnVuZHMtYTZlMDk4NTM_c3Q9dDNqZzh=
rcnd3dm03a2gxJnJlZmxpbms9ZGVza3RvcHdlYnNoYXJlX3Blcm1hbGluaw/607f07ceef4b852=
4a319a23cBfc5df9f6" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=
=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; bord=
er-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: so=
lid; background-color: #ccc;">constantly shooting at each other</a>:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Over the last 22 years, John Overdeck and Davi=
d Siegel built Two Sigma Investments into a $60 billion quant-trading behem=
oth. But behind the scenes, the billionaire co-founders have clashed over t=
he firm=E2=80=99s direction, succession planning and more, people familiar =
with the matter said. =C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The relationship has deteriorated to the point=
 where Two Sigma felt the need to disclose the friction in a March 31 <a hr=
ef=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/31848390.258405/aHR0cHM=
6Ly9maWxlcy5hZHZpc2VyaW5mby5zZWMuZ292L0lBUEQvQ29udGVudC9Db21tb24vY3JkX2lhcG=
RfQnJvY2h1cmUuYXNweD9CUkNIUl9WUlNOX0lEPTg0MzA1MQ/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB8=
d9425a4" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" s=
tyle=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-wid=
th: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; backgrou=
nd-color: #ccc;"> securities filing</a>. In a little-noticed section on =E2=
=80=9Cmaterial risks=E2=80=9D related to its investments strategies, the fi=
rm warned that Two Sigma=E2=80=99s management committee=E2=80=94which inclu=
des only Overdeck and Siegel=E2=80=94is having difficulty making key decisi=
ons, a disclosure that lawyers, investors and others say is virtually unpre=
cedented in the investment world. =E2=80=A6</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The executives, who have offices about 30 feet=
 from each other, split their duties. Overdeck has managed the investment r=
esearchers, or modelers, usually favoring a hands-off approach. Siegel over=
sees the firm=E2=80=99s engineers while appearing at industry conferences, =
often to speak about the future of artificial intelligence, which he studie=
d decades ago at MIT. Each executive has groups of loyalists within the fir=
m.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9CIt=E2=80=99s two tribes,=E2=80=9D sai=
d a person close to the firm. =E2=80=A6</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">In recent years, Overdeck and Siegel have rare=
ly appeared together at firm events. They frequently snipe at each other in=
 meetings, attendees said. Decisions get delayed and projects killed becaus=
e employees assume they won=E2=80=99t be able to get both founders to agree=
, the people said.=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">One person familiar with Overdeck and Siegel d=
escribed their relationship as evolving over the years =E2=80=9Cfrom irrita=
tion to Cold War to hot war.=E2=80=9D</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">There is another axis on which you can arrange=
 hedge funds, though: Some hedge funds have essentially systematic, compute=
r-driven, quant-y investment strategies, while others depend on the fundame=
ntal instincts of their portfolio managers (pirate captain or otherwise). T=
wo Sigma is quite firmly in the quant camp. I have a <a href=3D"https://lin=
k.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/31848390.258405/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21i=
ZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMTYtMDItMDUvYnJpZGdld2F0ZXItcy1ib3NzZXM=
tYXJlLWZpZ2h0aW5nLW92ZXItc29tZXRoaW5nP2NtcGlkPUJCRDA2MjAyM19NT05FWVNUVUZGJn=
V0bV9tZWRpdW09ZW1haWwmdXRtX3NvdXJjZT1uZXdzbGV0dGVyJnV0bV90ZXJtPTIzMDYyMCZ1d=
G1fY2FtcGFpZ249bW9uZXlzdHVmZg/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB92b66c19" itemprop=
=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #0=
00000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-b=
ottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">=
  half-joking model</a> for Bridgewater Associates, another quant-y firm, i=
n which:</p>
<ul style=3D"list-style-type: disc; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;">=
=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">The computer makes the investment deci=
sions,</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Freeing up the employees to=
 engage in a lot of bizarre interpersonal drama,</li>=09<li style=3D"margin=
-bottom: 5px;">Which in turn distracts=C2=A0them from interfering in the in=
vesting decisions, allowing the computer to just get down to work with perf=
ect rationality and no distractions.</li>
</ul>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Something like that seems to be happening at T=
wo Sigma, which is apparently paralyzed with interpersonal drama and yet ke=
eps investing just fine:</p>
<blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Some senior employees already have=
 left for competitors such as Citadel, but Two Sigma=E2=80=99s results rema=
in strong. There are few signs investors are pulling their investments, and=
 the firm is still profitable.</p></blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The fund=E2=80=99s managers can=E2=80=99t make=
 any decisions, but it turns out that=E2=80=99s for the best.</p>
